It has been fixed, but the problem is that the MV3 extension cannot update filters due to a Google policy. Therefore, the new rules will be available in an upcoming extension update.
Until then, please add following rules to user rules:
```adblock
hdfilmsitesi.*#%#//scriptlet('adjust-setTimeout', 'ifrld', '*', '0.001')
hdfilmsitesi.*#$##ifrld { display: block !important; }
hdfilmsitesi.*#$#body { background-image: none !important; }
hdfilmsitesi.*#$#div[style^="position: absolute; z-index: 1999999;"] { display: none !important; }
hdfilmsitesi.*#$#.duyuru_kutusu { display: none !important; }
hdfilmsitesi.*#$#.pageskin .oblong { margin-top: 0 !important; }
hdfilmsitesi.*#%#//scriptlet('trusted-create-element', 'head', 'script', '', '(()=>{window.addEventListener("load",(()=>{"function"==typeof window.ilk_part_getir&&window.ilk_part_getir()}));})();')
||hdfilmsitesi.me/?vr_set=1
```

Cannot reproduce with your settings. 

Please try following actions, then check the problem again:
1. Disable all content blockers in Safari settings and enable them again;
2. Restart Safari;
3. Restart AdGuard;
4. Check for filters update in AdGuard.

### Important:
<!-- **AdGuard для iOS** -->
* Do not close AdGuard window ~60 seconds, because iOS will break configuration process.
